Monday was tough. The bathtub couldn't fit all the tears. Hollow heart navigated reefs and dark reeds, bobbing up and down on the current as if made of balsa wood.

Tuesday was better. Took a walk to the grocery store and saw two people in the bathroom mirror. The first doesn't know how to shave and the second I found in a shadow on the return trip. I remembered everytime I felt something and how I got there.

Wednesday midnight pavement walking in preparation for consciousness conversion conversation after a quick libation station, athough not before space opera urge remediation. It's all the same, anyway.

Thursday ungreatful nearly-dead relenquished all power to all people. It was your face in the moonlight that convinced me it was possible.

